Package: NeStage
Title: Variance Effective Population Size for Stage-Structured Populations
Version: 0.7.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Raymond L.", "Tremblay",
           email = "raymond.tremblay@upr.edu",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8588-4372"))
Description: Computes the variance effective population size (Ne) for
    stage-structured plant and animal populations following the framework of
    Yonezawa et al. (2000) <doi:10.1111/j.0014-3820.2000.tb01243.x>.
    Three model functions cover clonal, sexual, and mixed (sexual + clonal)
    reproduction, all accepting a survival-transition matrix (MatU) and a
    fecundity vector (MatF row 1) as inputs. A suite of four sensitivity
    functions sweeps key parameters — sexual reproductive variance (Vk/k-bar),
    clonal reproductive variance (Vc/c-bar), clonal fraction (d), and
    generation time (L) — and returns ggplot2 figures and elasticity statistics
    to guide conservation decision-making. The package also reports the minimum
    census size needed to achieve a user-specified Ne target and the estimated
    Ne at a user-supplied census population size.
